POST-INSTALL:
		* Create a link to the plugin:
		ln -sf /usr/lib/tclplugin/plugins/libnptcl3.1.so /PATH_TO_FIREFOX_OR_MOZILLA_INSTALL_DIR/plugins/

USAGE:

		* Problem with focus:
		Firefox/Mozilla doesn't like giving focus to the plugin (tclet) on Unix/Linux.
		Once the plugin is loaded, if you've to interact with the tclet (usually with keystroke), 
		you must first, click outside Firefox/Mozilla and then back to get focus.
 
INFO:

		* The best wiki resource about tclplugin:
		http://wiki.tcl.tk/12719

		* Try some cool tclets here:
		http://wiki.tcl.tk/10696
		http://www.tcl.tk/software/plugin/applets.html

WIN32:

		* An up to date web site:
		http://www.tcl.tk/software/plugin/

		* You can get the Win32 plugin for Firefox/Mozilla at:
		http://tkoutline.sourceforge.net/tclplugin.xpi

		* Even for IE, install it from:
		http://www.gamon.org/Profession/TCL/tclplugin30_002.exe
